{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17414207","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17414207"},"attributes":{"position":33,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T08:43:17+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T08:43:17+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16961"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17564270","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17564270"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:11:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:11:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16961"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261100"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:28:52+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":62,"questionsAnswered":61,"marksTotal":61,"marksAttainable":61,"marksAttempted":61,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T09:15:31+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.2,"questionsCorrect":12,"marksCorrect":12},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"16961","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16961"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.7,0.04,0.07,0.08,0.1]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9651"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67985"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9651","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9651"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16961"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53450"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"22"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1196"},{"type":"tags","id":"1315"},{"type":"tags","id":"4111"},{"type":"tags","id":"4983"},{"type":"tags","id":"11643"},{"type":"tags","id":"12801"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"22767"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41001"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43675"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67985","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67985"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic requesting contraception. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. She has never been pregnant. She is a non-smoker with a body mass index of 22 kg/m2. She exercises regularly and works as an accountant. On examination, she appears well with vital signs within normal limits.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following combined oral contraceptive pill formulations should be recommended to this patient being associated with the lowest risk of venous thromboembolism?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["30\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with levonorgestrel","35\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with cyproterone","50\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with levonorgestrel","30\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with desogestrel","35\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with drospirenone"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe risk of venous thromboembolism (VTE) with combined oral contraceptive pills (COCPs) is influenced by both the dose of ethinylestradiol and the type of progestogen. Lower doses of ethinylestradiol are associated with lower thrombotic risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E30\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with levonorgestrel\u003C/strong\u003E has the lowest risk of VTE among the options presented. Levonorgestrel is a second-generation progestogen with a well-established safety profile. The combination of a lower oestrogen dose (30\u03bcg) with levonorgestrel represents the safest COCP formulation regarding VTE risk.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E50\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with levonorgestrel\u003C/strong\u003E carries a higher VTE risk due to the higher oestrogen dose. Higher doses of ethinylestradiol are associated with increased thrombotic risk and are no longer recommended as first-line options.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E35\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with cyproterone\u003C/strong\u003E has approximately a 6-8 times increased risk of VTE compared to non-users, higher than levonorgestrel-containing pills. Cyproterone is an anti-androgenic progestogen primarily used for treating acne.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E35\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with drospirenone\u003C/strong\u003E carries a higher VTE risk than levonorgestrel-containing pills. Drospirenone is a fourth-generation progestogen with anti-mineralocorticoid properties.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E30\u03bcg ethinylestradiol with desogestrel\u003C/strong\u003E, while containing a lower oestrogen dose, is associated with a higher VTE risk than levonorgestrel-containing pills as desogestrel is a third-generation progestogen.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhen prescribing COCPs, it is important to consider individual risk factors for VTE including age, smoking status, obesity, and family history. The absolute risk of VTE in young, healthy women remains low, but choosing a formulation with the lowest possible risk is prudent.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Combined oral contraceptive pills containing \u226430\u03bcg ethinylestradiol have lower thrombotic risk than higher-dose formulations.","Risk factors for thrombosis on combined oral contraceptive pills include smoking, obesity, and age over 35 years.","Combined oral contraceptive pills are associated with a small increased risk of breast cancer and cardiovascular events."],"references":["Royal Australian and New Zealand College of Obstetricians and Gynaecologists (RANZCOG). Contraception [Internet]. Melbourne: RANZCOG; 2023 [cited 2024 Jun 23]. Available from: https://ranzcog.edu.au/wp-content/uploads/Contraception-Clinical-Guideline.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53450"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16961"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53450","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53450"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-08T12:47:00+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-08T12:48:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9651"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67985"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"22","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/22"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf53","name":"Gynaecology","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"3"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"72","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/72"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Graduating","synonyms":null,"description":"Only suitabl